php-sfcgal (1.0.1+git20260427-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Gap-fix release based on Geodesy-side feedback.
    - SFCGALGeometry::BUFFER3D_{ROUND,CYLSPHERE,FLAT} class constants.
    - Multi* now extend SFCGALGeometryCollection (per OGC SF),
      inheriting addGeometry() / setGeometryN().  Fixes the
      "addGeometry not found on MultiPolygon" issue.
    - SFCGALMultiSolid::create() registered.
    - New SFCGALGeometry::decomposeToFaces(): SFCGALMultiPolygon —
      flatten Solid / *Surface / MultiSolid / Triangle to face
      polygons.  Used internally by toGEOS() to bridge 3D-only types
      that SFCGAL/GEOS cannot WKB-roundtrip natively.
    - fromGEOS() forces ISO WKB flavor on the internal GEOSWKBWriter
      so SFCGAL parses what GEOS emits.
    - Internal: explicit __construct invocation on GEOSWKB{Reader,
      Writer} proxy objects (relay setup happens in the constructor).
    - tests/009_BridgeAndDecompose.phpt regression coverage.

 -- Abraham van der Merwe <abz@frogfoot.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 23:30:00 +0200

php-sfcgal (1.0.0+git20260427-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Initial release: PHP bindings for SFCGAL 2.2.0.
    - Flat-namespace classes (matching the php-geos style):
      SFCGALGeometry (abstract), SFCGALPoint, SFCGALLineString,
      SFCGALPolygon, SFCGALMultiPoint, SFCGALMultiLineString,
      SFCGALMultiPolygon, SFCGALGeometryCollection, SFCGALTriangle,
      SFCGALTriangulatedSurface, SFCGALPolyhedralSurface, SFCGALSolid,
      SFCGALMultiSolid, SFCGALPreparedGeometry, SFCGALException.
    - 165+ methods covering OGC SF3D: intersects3D / intersection3D /
      difference3D / union3D / convexHull3D / distance3D / area3D /
      length3D / volume / centroid3D / covers3D, plus tesselate,
      extrude, makeSolid, triangulate2DZ, straightSkeleton family,
      alphaShapes / optimalAlphaShapes / alphaWrapping3D, buffer3D,
      visibilityPoint / visibilitySegment, partition_2 family,
      rotate / scale / translate variants, and full WKT/WKB/EWKT/
      hex-WKB/OBJ/STL/VTK I/O.
    - Bridge to/from GEOSGeometry via WKB round-trip; rejects curved
      types (CircularString / CompoundCurve / CurvePolygon /
      MultiCurve / MultiSurface) with a hint to call
      GEOSGeometry::curveToLine() first — same behaviour as PostGIS
      LWGEOM2SFCGAL.
    - Built against SFCGAL 2.2.0 + CGAL 6.1.1 on Ubuntu Jammy / PHP 8.1.
    - 9 .phpt tests; 100 percent green.

 -- Abraham van der Merwe <abz@frogfoot.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 16:00:00 +0200
